\fs22 \cf2 I need to build a 3D Printer Production Simulator. Here is the specification: Objective\
Build a software system that simulates, day by day, the full production cycle of a factory that\
manufactures 3D printers. The focus is on inventory management, purchasing, and production\
planning. The user plays the role of production planner: they decide what to manufacture\
and what to buy.\
Functional Requirements (Minimum)\
R0 \'97 Initial Configuration\
Define the production plan: - Bill of Materials (BOM) for each printer model (what raw materials\
are needed, in what quantities) - Assembly time per model - Supplier catalog: products for sale,\
prices by quantity (e.g., per pallet of 1000 units, per box of 20), lead time for delivery - Warehouse\
capacity (simplified: 1 unit of any material = 1 storage unit)\
R1 \'97 Demand Generation\
At the start of each simulated day, manufacturing orders are generated randomly. Parameters\
(mean and variance) must be configurable.\
R2 \'97 Control Dashboard\
Display: - Pending orders - Bill of Materials breakdown for each order - Current inventory levels\
R3 \'97 User Decisions\
The user must be able to: - Release orders to production - Issue purchase orders (choose product,\
supplier, quantity, and date)\
R4 \'97 Event Simulation\
\'95 Raw material consumption during manufacturing, limited by daily capacity\
\'95 Purchase arrivals according to supplier lead time\
R5 \'97 Calendar Advance\
A button \'93Advance Day\'94 runs the 24h simulation cycle.\
R6 \'97 Event Log\
Record all events for historical tracking and charts.\
R7 \'97 JSON Import/Export\
Export and import inventory state and event history as JSON.\
R8 \'97 REST API\
Every piece of functionality and information shown in the UI must be accessible via a REST API\
documented with Swagger / OpenAPI.\
Non-Functional Requirements\
\'95 Clean, commented code versioned with Git\
\'95 Simple web interface; no complex client-side installation\
\'95 Cross-platform (Windows, macOS, Linux). \
Help me create a Product Requirements Document (PRD) that covers: the data model,\
the architecture, the tech stack decisions, the API endpoints, and a development plan with\
milestones. Ask me clarifying questions before drafting.\
\
\
